Script,FoundRabbisRule
window.currentPBSScenario = 'FoundRabbisRule';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Found_Rabbis_Rule';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for FoundRabbisRule');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'FoundRabbisRule',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge
auction-filter: Auction.....
*/
# bba-direct: true
# auction-filter: Auction.....
# convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
# convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge

action printoneline,
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Found Rabbi\'s Rule,\n\
--- Found Rabbi's Rule (4!S) — curated hands where the safety play applies\n\
\n\
These hands are extracted from Rabbis_Rule.pbn by [find_rabbis_rule_makers.py]:\n\
contract = 4!S，declarer = South，result >= 10 tricks (declarer made the\n\
contract). Each hand demonstrates Rabbi's Rule —\n\
\n\
  "When the King is singleton，play the Ace."\n\
\n\
West holds the singleton !D K. East holds the !H KQ threat. To make\n\
4!S，declarer must drop West's bare K rather than finesse for it.\n\
\n\
Things to think about:\n\
• Count your tricks before touching the trump suit.\n\
• If you have 10 top tricks on the safety play，take them — don't\n\
  finesse for an 11th and risk going down.\n\
• The safety play here is dropping the singleton King.\n\
\n\
Reference: https://www.bridgebum.com/safety-plays.php\n\
%FoundRabbisRule%,backgroundColor=lightpink
